    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-01T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.94/307h</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-01T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5175. War Industries Board is sending abroad a group in connection with
                    arrangements for the participation of that Board in the discussion of
                    inter-Allied organizations being formed in Paris and London. Personnel of this
                    mission comprises Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SLL1">Leland L. Summers</persName>,
                    member of the Board, who will act as head of the mission, Mr. <persName>Chandler
                        P. Anderson</persName>, counsel for the War Industries Board on
                    international matters, Mr. <persName>George N. Armsby</persName>, Mr.
                        <persName>Albert M. Patterson</persName>, Mr. <persName>Lincoln
                        Hutchinson</persName>, Mr. <persName>John Hughes</persName>, Mr.
                        <persName>Edward A. Pierce</persName>, Mr. <persName>Paul
                    Mackall</persName>, Mr. <persName>Frederick K. Mxon</persName>, Mr.
                        <persName>Arthur D. Whiteside</persName>, Mr. <persName>Henry W.
                        Boyd</persName>, Mr. <persName>Hubert H. Brooker</persName>, Mr.
                        <persName>Philio B. Gait</persName> and Mr. <persName>James Bernard
                        Mahoney</persName>. This mission is only for the purpose of exchanging views
                    and final action as result of this exchange is to be referred back here for any
                    necessary decision.</p>
                <p>Please communicate this information to French Government and repeat to Embassy
                    London for its information and that of the British Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
